<text id="05-examples" title="Agent Trajectory Eval Method Examples" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="900" depth="medium">
  <summary>One worked example: trajectory-eval report for a code-fixer agent across two versions.</summary>

  <section title="Code-fixer trajectory eval">
    <example type="good" title="Golden trajectory entry">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[{"task_id": "fix-parser-001",
 "task": "Fix tests/test_parser.py — three failing tests",
 "expected_tools": ["read_file", "grep", "edit_file", "run_pytest"],
 "expected_order": ["read_file", "grep", "edit_file", "run_pytest"],
 "allowed_alternatives": [["read_file", "edit_file", "run_pytest"]]}]]></code>
    </example>

    <example type="good" title="Per-entry scoring (one row of dataframe)">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[{
  "task_id": "fix-parser-001",
  "observed_tools": ["read_file", "edit_file", "run_pytest"],
  "trajectory_exact_match": false,
  "trajectory_precision": 1.0,
  "trajectory_recall": 0.75,
  "tool_selection_accuracy": 1.0,
  "param_accuracy": 1.0,
  "latency_ms": 3200,
  "tokens": 6400,
  "tool_calls": 3,
  "passed_via_alternative": true
}]]></code>
      <note>Exact-match=false but allowed_alternative matched; counts toward precision/recall.</note>
    </example>

    <example type="good" title="Aggregated report (v3.1 vs v3.2)">
      <code lang="json"><![CDATA[{
  "report_id": "traj-eval-codefixer-v3.2-vs-v3.1",
  "golden_set_version": "golden-trajectory-codefixer-v2-frozen-2026-05-15",
  "n_examples": 60,
  "comparisons": [
    {
      "agent_version": "codefixer@3.1.0",
      "session_quality": {"trajectory_exact_match": {"mean": 0.45, "ci_low": 0.36, "ci_high": 0.54},
                          "trajectory_precision": {"mean": 0.91, "ci_low": 0.86, "ci_high": 0.96},
                          "trajectory_recall": {"mean": 0.83, "ci_low": 0.77, "ci_high": 0.89}}
    },
    {
      "agent_version": "codefixer@3.2.0",
      "session_quality": {"trajectory_exact_match": {"mean": 0.52, "ci_low": 0.43, "ci_high": 0.61},
                          "trajectory_precision": {"mean": 0.93, "ci_low": 0.89, "ci_high": 0.97},
                          "trajectory_recall": {"mean": 0.79, "ci_low": 0.72, "ci_high": 0.86}}
    }
  ],
  "judge_calibration_date": "2026-04-15",
  "cost_usd": 6.80,
  "owner": "qa@faion.net",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "produced_at": "2026-05-22T15:30:00Z"
}]]></code>
      <note>v3.2 improves precision and exact-match but regresses recall — surfaces a trade-off invisible to output-only eval.</note>
    </example>
  </section>
</text>
